THIRD-PARTY COMPONENTS
======================

The DeltaT installer ships a self-contained build, so the following components
are redistributed inside it. Their licenses are reproduced or linked below, and
each remains the property of its respective authors.

LibreHardwareMonitorLib (0.9.6)
  https://github.com/LibreHardwareMonitor/LibreHardwareMonitor
  Mozilla Public License 2.0 (https://mozilla.org/MPL/2.0/)

  DeltaT uses this library unmodified, exactly as published on NuGet. The
  library's source, including the version DeltaT builds against, is available
  from the project page above. MPL-2.0 covered files remain under MPL-2.0; this
  program as a whole is distributed under the GPL, as MPL-2.0 section 3.3
  permits.

  DeltaT reads sensors through this library. It does not bundle a kernel driver:
  the PawnIO driver is a separate product, installed by its own signed installer
  from its own author. See the security section of the README.

Hardcodet.NotifyIcon.Wpf (2.x)
  https://github.com/hardcodet/wpf-notifyicon
  MIT License

CommunityToolkit.Mvvm (8.x)
  https://github.com/CommunityToolkit/dotnet
  MIT License

Microsoft.Data.Sqlite (8.x), System.Management (10.x), and the .NET runtime
  https://github.com/dotnet
  MIT License

SQLite itself is in the public domain (https://sqlite.org/copyright.html).


SERVICES
========

DeltaT queries the following services at runtime. They are not redistributed and
are subject to their own terms.

Open-Meteo (https://open-meteo.com) for outside temperature.
BigDataCloud (https://www.bigdatacloud.com) for reverse geocoding a place name.
